Your Honor,

I stand before this court today to express my guilt and take full responsibility for my actions. I am pleading guilty to the charge of accepting a bribe in exchange for not publishing an article exposing a company's false claims about their CO2 emissions.

I want to acknowledge the severity of my offense. I accepted a total of 4000 pounds in exchange for not publishing an article where I had found that this company emits one million tonnes of CO2 more per year than what they claim. The bribe allowed the company to continue their greenwashing practices for a short period of time, until the true numbers were released by another source just five weeks later.

I must stress that I have a previous speeding ticket, unrelated to this current charge. While I understand that this may not be considered a mitigating factor, I would like to emphasize that I have otherwise maintained a clean record up until now in terms of criminal offenses.

I offer no excuses for my actions and take full responsibility for succumbing to temptation and accepting the bribe. I did not actively seek out the bribe but was approached by individuals who offered me the money in exchange for not publishing the article.

In conclusion, I humbly request the court's understanding and leniency in sentencing, considering the impact of my actions, my acknowledgement of guilt, and my previously clean record. Thank you for your attention to this matter.

